# template.nix Content

Based on the GitHub page, here's the full content of `template.nix` from the Comamoca/scaffold repository:

```nix
{
  flake-devenv = {
    path = ./flake-devenv;
    description = "Nix flake with devenv template.";
  };
  flake-basic = {
    path = ./flake-basic;
    description = "Nix flake basic template.";
  };
  c-cli = {
    path = ./c-cli;
    description = "Basic C project template.";
  };
  c-raylib-cmake = {
    path = ./c-raylib-cmake;
    description = "Raylib project build with cmake.";
  };
  deno-hono = {
    path = ./deno-hono;
    description = "Hono project with Deno.";
  };
  haxe-basic-cpp = {
    path = ./haxe-basic-cpp;
    description = "Haxe project with cpp target.";
  };
  honox-minimal = {
    path = ./honox-minimal;
    description = "Minimal HonoX project.";
  };
  odin-hello = {
    path = ./odin-hello;
    description = "Minimal Odin project.";
  };
  cl-nix = {
    path = ./cl-nix;
    description = "Common Lisp with Nix";
  };
  gleam-basic = {
    path = ./gleam-basic;
    description = "A basic flake to with Gleam language";
  };
}
```

This file defines a set of Nix flake templates for various programming languages and frameworks, each with a local path reference and descriptive label.

